

 Q2. Explain the difference between Spring-MVC and Spring Boot.

 Answer)    1. Spring MVC is a Model View, and Controller based web framework widely used to develop web applications.
 
			2. Spring Boot is built on top of the conventional spring framework, widely used to develop REST APIs.
			
			3. We need to build the configuration manually in Spring MVC.
			
			4. There is no need to build the configuration manually in Spring Boot.
			
			5. A deployment descriptor is required in Spring MVC.
			
			6. There is no need for a deployment descriptor in Spring Boot.
			
			7. Spring MVC framework consists of four components : Model, View, Controller, and Front Controller.
			
			8. There are four main layers in Spring Boot: Presentation Layer, Data Access Layer, Service Layer, and Integration Layer.